Dessert was also small in portion but ok in taste. Honestly deciding whether I should call my credit card company for a refund which I feel the restaurant owes me for terrible overpriced food. Avoid this place and try your luck elsewhere along the Jersey waterfront. The hype is not worth hurting your pocket over. Attended here on Dec 21, 2020 for a party of 8 birthday dinner. What we enjoyed upon entering the establishment was the safety precautions and contact less approach with signing the nondisclosure agreement, and accessible menus online. There were a number of discrepancies that were not specified and some of the staff are not on the same page when information is conveyed. When making reservations online with OpenTable it stated for parties 7 or more a three hour + time limit. On the Ventanas website and mini table menu it indicates for all parties due to Covid, there is an hour and a half seating arrangement for all parties. We were advised by our server that the hour and a half was true due to the new restrictions, they would ensure our food would come out in a timely manner and we would be able to enjoy everything. Our group ordered an array of food; lobster dumplings, octopus and chorizo kabobs, k-town wings, dragon rolls, and a round of drinks. Our drinks came with in 15 minutes with water served immediately. The lobster dumplings were okay, slightly undercooked, and we tasted more cilantro then lobster itself. The octopus and chorizo kabobs were slightly cold, and the k-town wings were a bit tough to chew. I would assume because they are cooked in a broiler quickly and tossed in a sauce that was a tad bit salty.The sushi was amazing! I would say the servers were very attentive at first. The problems began to arise when our food was being rushed out due to trying to maintain the time ordnance under the Covid restrictions. At this point we were already there for over an hour our appetizers came out behind schedule due to the sushi bar being backed up. We knew things weren't going to go as planned as errors occur, totally understandable. By the time the entrées came out it was already passed an hour. We ordered; (2)miso salmon one cooked medium and the other well, (2) rack of ribs one with shrimp and the other with fries, (2) branzino and artichoke puree, a steak and their special vegan meal. Now here is where the problem arises, our food came back and the size of the salmon was disappointing for the amount of money being spent paired with the vegetable fried rice that only had scallions in it and the rice was plated as if one scoop was thinly stretched across the plate. Not to mention the salmon was dry. You could tell it was rushed out. The menu indicated rack of ribs and we assumed we would get a rack if not half a rack. The rack consisted of 3 baby back ribs (to be honest they were the smallest pieces and could easily equal 2 ribs total for $35 dollars per plate) each and what appeared to be bland cocktail shrimp with one of the orders.When I brought this to the staffs attention we were advised 4 ribs come with a rack by one staff member and 3 from another. Once the manager was called we were told  a "rack of ribs" was defined as multiple. The manager was able to comp. our order by adding additional 4 ribs to both meals and recreate one of the miso salmon dishes. This time the order looked totally different and looked like a quality meal was produced. We were pleased although felt like for the amount of money was being spent that should of never happened to begin with even under pressure in the kitchen. People leave any establishment with the following in mind; service, food, and drinks. Collectively we thought some things were okay, however we won't be back.
